Children.Text: This model does not consider plant mortality.
Children.Name: Memo

Children.Text: Age is the age of the planting in years.
Children.Name: Memo

Children.Text: This model uses standard days rather than a thermal time and so a value of 1 is used for each day.
Children.Name: Memo

Children.Text: This model assumes that all senesced leaves detach immediately.
Children.Name: Memo

Children.Text: Value of 1.06 g/MJ for above ground growth from [HarringtonAndFownes1995] is increased to account for biomass partitioning to below-ground organs.
Children.Name: Memo

Children.Text: Use same value as determined for live leaves.
Children.Name: Memo

Children.Text: Assume leaves have a life span of approximately half a year.
Children.Name: Memo

Children.Text: This model assumes that all leaves detach upon senescence.
Children.Name: Memo

Children.Text: Leaf cohorts age according to a simple aggregation of time (ie no accounting for differing rates of development with temperature or stress).
Children.Name: Memo

Children.Text: This model does not account for any change in potential water uptake with plant development.
Children.Name: Memo

Children.Text: This model does not account for any change in potential NO3 uptake with plant development.
Children.Name: Memo

Children.Text: This model does not account for any change in potential NH4 uptake with plant development.
Children.Name: Memo

Children.Text: This model calculated the N supply from biological N fixation by nodules within the plant root system.
Children.Name: Memo
